{
  "stem": "24397.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And some people helped us find jobs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then gradually I found my-- my own ways.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I found that the Habonim youth movement had-- it was a Zionist youth movement-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] had a lot of the answers to things that I was looking for in life.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I found lots of friends there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I also found that after having lived in England for five, six years or more and almost forgotten or not thinking of myself as a refugee anymore, all of a sudden I became one in the eyes of these people.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But in London, I wasn't looked upon like that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was-- that was hard at first.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But pretty soon I made lots of friends there in Manchester.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I enjoyed-- very much enjoyed the life then.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I'm still in touch with some of the people from there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then the British government made a gesture to children such as we who had lost their parents.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And they offered them British nationality without them having to go through the normal thing of publications or writing and applying and all that.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "All you had to do was just say yes, sign a piece of paper, and that's it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So we both did that and became British.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then everything went along fine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when I was about 18 or before 18, 17 and 1/2, I got my call-up papers, so I went to have my medical and tests and all that sort of thing, and I passed that.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They said, OK, we'll notify you when-- when we want you.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Meanwhile, the situation in Israel, or Palestine then, was-- was changing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The war had started.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
